<paragraph id="8B870F6D65708626FF4CDFCCFE5CFE60" blockId="12.[151,1436,1951,2014]" lastBlockId="13.[151,1437,152,611]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="342" pageId="12" pageNumber="341">
<emphasis id="B94CD37F65708627FF4CDFCCFEBDF850" bold="true" box="[151,334,1951,1978]" pageId="12" pageNumber="341">Common name</emphasis>
. ‘ 
<collectingCountry id="F32F4FFD65708627FEBBDFF3FDD3F850" box="[352,544,1952,1978]" name="Solomon Islands" pageId="12" pageNumber="341">Solomon Islands</collectingCountry>
delicate lacewing’. 
<emphasis id="B94CD37F65708627FF1CDF90FEB1F834" bold="true" box="[199,322,1987,2014]" pageId="12" pageNumber="341">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Forewing spot round, located on inner gradate series close to main stem branch of RP; hind wing 
<subSubSection id="C3225CE665718626FF4CD8CBFE5CFE60" pageId="13" pageNumber="342" type="description">pterostigma with small distinct spot, and small dark spot midway along inner gradate series, otherwise with dark suffusion along inner-most and middle gradate series; forewing with three gradate series, hind wing with two gradate series; forewing RA area with RA-RP cross-veins simple (rarely forked), lacking interconnecting cross-veins; basal half of forewing with irregular cross-veins connecting RP branches, lacking in hind wing; forewing innermost gradates series broadly curved, angled strongly at mid point; middle (shorter) gradate series of hind wing only slightly curved (not connected to inner gradate series basally); end-twigging only present along posterior margin in distal half of both wings.</subSubSection>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3225CE665718626FF1CD9C7FD4BFD88" pageId="13" pageNumber="342" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B870F6D65718626FF1CD9C7FD4BFD88" blockId="13.[151,1437,152,611]" pageId="13" pageNumber="342">
<emphasis id="B94CD37F65718626FF1CD9C7FEBCFE45" bold="true" box="[199,335,404,431]" pageId="13" pageNumber="342">Comments.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C3874EE65718626FE8ED9C7FDB6FE44" baseAuthorityName="Kimmins" baseAuthorityYear="1951" box="[341,581,404,430]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Apochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="342" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salomonis">
<emphasis id="B94CD37F65718626FE8ED9C7FDB6FE44" box="[341,581,404,430]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="342">Apochrysa salomonis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to the other Oceania species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3874EE65718626FC21D9C6FB81FE44" baseAuthorityName="Kimmins" baseAuthorityYear="1953" box="[1018,1138,405,431]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Apochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="342" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cognata">
<emphasis id="B94CD37F65718626FC21D9C6FB81FE44" box="[1018,1138,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="342">A. cognata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3874EE65718626FB7CD9C6FAA6FE44" baseAuthorityName="Girard" baseAuthorityYear="1862" box="[1191,1365,405,431]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Apochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="342" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="montrouzieri">
<emphasis id="B94CD37F65718626FB7CD9C6FAA6FE44" box="[1191,1365,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="342">A. montrouzieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; these were previously placed together with 
<taxonomicName id="4C3874EE65718626FDE6D9EAFD46FE38" box="[573,693,440,467]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Apochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="342" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="evanida">
<emphasis id="B94CD37F65718626FDE6D9EAFD46FE38" box="[573,693,440,467]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="342">A. evanida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C3874EE65718626FC91D9EBFC12FE38" authority="Needham, 1909" authorityName="Needham" authorityYear="1909" box="[842,993,440,466]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Synthochrysa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="342" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94CD37F65718626FC91D9EBFC12FE38" box="[842,993,440,466]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="342">Synthochrysa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFA9729C65718626FC34D9EBFB5AFE39" author="Kimmins, D. E." box="[1007,1193,440,467]" pageId="13" pageNumber="342" pagination="780 - 785" refId="ref8897" refString="Kimmins, D. E. (1951) New species of Neuroptera from the Solomon Islands. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 12, 4 (44), 780 - 785. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222935108654205" type="journal article" year="1951">Kimmins (1951)</bibRefCitation>
originally placed this species in 
<taxonomicName id="4C3874EE65718626FED2D98FFE85FE1C" authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1913" box="[265,374,476,502]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Nobilinus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="342" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94CD37F65718626FED2D98FFE85FE1C" box="[265,374,476,502]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="342">Nobilinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C3874EE65718626FE58D98FFD81FE1C" baseAuthorityName="Kimmins" baseAuthorityYear="1951" box="[387,626,476,502]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Apochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="342" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salomonis">
<emphasis id="B94CD37F65718626FE58D98FFD81FE1C" box="[387,626,476,502]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="342">Apochrysa salomonis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from other members of the genus by the dark, round spots on the inner gradate series of both wings, as well as three gradate series in the forewing and two gradate series in the hind wing. 
<taxonomicName id="4C3874EE65718626FEBDDA77FDAAFDD4" baseAuthorityName="Kimmins" baseAuthorityYear="1951" box="[358,601,548,574]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysopidae" genus="Apochrysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="342" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salomonis">
<emphasis id="B94CD37F65718626FEBDDA77FDAAFDD4" box="[358,601,548,574]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="342">Apochrysa salomonis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from Guadacanal, 
<collectingCountry id="F32F4FFD65718626FC73DA77FB99FDD4" box="[936,1130,548,574]" name="Solomon Islands" pageId="13" pageNumber="342">Solomon Islands</collectingCountry>
. The 
<typeStatus id="5483B1CF65718626FB70DA77FAFEFDD4" box="[1195,1293,548,574]" pageId="13" pageNumber="342">holotype</typeStatus>
specimen is housed in the Natural History Museum, London.
</paragraph>
